  heading: CRO
  details: 'A CRO (Cathode Ray Oscilloscope) experiment is used to observe and measure
    electrical waveforms.

    It helps determine voltage, frequency, and phase relationships
    in AC signals.

    By analyzing the displayed trace, students learn how signals
    vary over time and how electronic circuits behave.'
